@NickADobos The biggest challenge any new competitor to GitHub has is building trust

I need my code hosting service to maintain stable URLs and not lose my data. GitHub has 17 years of track record on this.

A competitor launched today won't have 17 years track record for another 17 years!

The notion of what "writing code" is is starting to get very confusing to me.

@simonw wrote about how he has Go running in production, despite not knowing Go.  And how he's written JavaScript widgets to use async/await, without deep JavaScript expertise.

@Steve_Yegge wrote about how he's writing things in TypeScript, despite not having tons of TypeScript experience.

Here's my story of how I did a statistical analysis that was important to me in 90m using Python/Scikit-Learn in @GoogleColab, despite having never used pandas, scikit-learn, barely used a Jupyter notebook, and very little Python.

The world of "writing code" is getting really strange.

